!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

downward /ˈdaʊnwəd/

1. ADJ A downward movement or look is directed toward a lower place or a lower level. 向下的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...a firm downward movement of the hands. …一个坚定有力的双手向下的动作。 

2. ADJ If you refer to a downward trend, you mean that something is decreasing or that a situation is getting worse. 逐渐下降的; 日趋恶化的 [ADJ n] 

例： The downward trend in home ownership is likely to continue. 住房拥有率的下降趋势有可能还要延续。 

3. ADV If you move or look downward , you move or look toward the ground or a lower level. 朝下地 

例： Benedict pointed downward again with his stick. 贝内迪克特又用他的拐杖向下指了指。 

4. ADV If an amount or rate moves downward , it decreases. 下降地 [ADV after v] 

例： Inflation is moving firmly downward. 通货膨胀在稳步下降。 

5. ADV If you want to emphasize that a statement applies to everyone in an organization, you can say that it applies from its leader downward . 往下地 ['from' n ADV] [强调] 

例： ...from the president downward. …自总经理而下。

</div>

